main event: On August 8, 1955, an unidentified object was observed in Fresno, California, between 2345 and 0040 hours.
interesting points: The object was observed as slower than normal air traffic and showed no lights., The observer stated that the object was unidentified., An additional witness suspected it was a meteor., The report concluded there was insufficient data for evaluation., The sighting was categorized under Project Blue Book for further investigation.
witness description: The observer reported observing the object visually from the ground.
